\i  me
\i0 ! She must've been embarrassed, I guess.\
31 P\uc0\u97 \u772 -\u603 \u769 : Because you just haven't gotten to know each other yet.\
32 C\'e0-l\uc0\u596 \u770 : Probably so, that's probably it.\
33 P\uc0\u97 \u772 -\u603 \u769 : After two or three nights, she'll probably get friendlier.\
34 Th\'fb-y\'ec: Well, with me now, as far as conversation goes, when I go over there she talks to me even if I sit on the ground without even going into her house!\
35 C\'e0-l\uc0\u596 \u770 : Won't you please explain to me how you do it? Since I've never heard [anything about how it's done]!\
36 Th\'fb-y\'ec: Oh, boy![9]\
37 C\'e0-l\uc0\u596 \u770 : When you go, what's the first thing you say to the girl?\
38 P\uc0\u97 \u772 -\u603 \u769 : You take a stick and poke it through from underneath the floor.[10] When she comes out you say "Have a chat with me!"\
39 C\'e0-l\uc0\u596 \u770 : You say "Have a chat with me," eh?\
40 P\uc0\u97 \u772 -\u603 \u769 , Th\'fb-y\'ec\}: Right, right.\
41 C\'e0-l\uc0\u596 \u770 : Then what does she say[11] to you?\
42 Th\'fb-y\'ec: She says, "You say something first! What have you been thinking about?" But 
\i we
\i0  have to tell her about our feelings.[12]\
43 C\'e0-l\uc0\u596 \u770 : What sort of thing?\
44 Th\'fb-y\'ec: Whether we love her or not. She listens to what we say to her. \
45 P\uc0\u97 \u772 -\u603 \u769 : We've got to tell her, "I love you!"\
46 C\'e0-l\uc0\u596 \u770 : You've got to say, "I love you," huh?\
47 P\uc0\u97 \u772 -\u603 \u769 : Yes.\
48 C\'e0-l\uc0\u596 \u770 : Can't you say, "I don't love you"?\
49 P\uc0\u97 \u772 -\u603 \u769 : If we say, "I don't love you," then they won't love us either.\
50 C\'e0-l\uc0\u596 \u770 : Hmm.\
